  "title": "",
  "body": "  Amina from Kenya wants to buy a mobile phone from the United States.     In Kenya, she uses Kenyan Shillings (KSh).    In the United States, people use US Dollars ($).    To buy the phone, Amina needs to exchange her Kenyan Shillings for US Dollars.    This is because each country uses its own currency for buying and selling goods and services.    Why?       Different countries use different currencies to manage their own economies and trade with other countries.   "
